review_blob: Poors a deep almost black red. Held to the lights brilliant mohogony. Aroma of slight pine, fruity hops and sweet toffee malt. Aroma flavour and taste combine in a well balanced bitter sweet fruity strong malt ale. Very tasty!
Nice well made beer. Golden poor. Nice white head that disappears shortly after poor. Big fruity ale. Smooth and clean. Nice easy drinking ipa
Big flavoursome ipa. Nice sparkling clear golden poor. Big tropical fruit. Crisp bitter and clean. Dangerously drinkable at 11%.
Great full flavoured ale. Aroma of orange and citrus. Flavour is pleasant fruity. Nice amount of bitterness on the back palate. Happily drunk a couple of these.
Big tasty beer with a nice pine and slight tropical aroma. Flavour is similar with the resinous hops and tropical fruit combining nicely. Taste is really good big bitterness, dry. Very nice.

Poors a clear straw yellow with minimal fizzy white head. Aroma is slight tropical hops which follow through into the flavour only just. Disappointed with the hop aroma and flavour, could have had another bag full of hops. Very refreshing, easy to drink though. Perfect for a couple over a bbq. Malt is clean, dry and although there is not as much flavour the beer disappears quickly.
POors a nice clear amber orange. Aroma of pine and citrus. Very big flavour of pine resin and citrus. Nice clean level of bitterness. Very tasty easily drinkable.

Poors a superb deep red nice head that sticks to the glass. Aroma is big floral citrus hops mixed in with woody bourban just slightly. Taste is big and bitter but has a nice mellowness. Flavours is full hop citrus and thick. Some nice bourban flavours but not as big as I was expecting.
Another very nice beer.

Big pine, resin grass hop bomb. I like it. Tasty full on beer. Poorer a deep red, off white head. Aroma big hop pine resin and a little into the hoppy grass. Flavour followed on from aroma. Taste was pleasantly bitter. Nice malt back bone. Very tasty and a bit boozy.

Great deep clear amber poor with a just off white head. Not an over the top aroma but pleasant sweetness some fruit and pine. Toffee, pine, sweet and bitter all really nicely balanced in this tasty beverage. Really nice just over all really pleasant beverage.

Poors a hazy hay colour. Nice puffy white head but carbonation is not as lively as I was expecting. Aroma of banana, saison yeast and farmhouse. Taste is nice dry full flavoured and disappears to quickly! Very nice refreshing summer beer.

Poors clear deep golden brown with small night white head lingering. Aroma is full of pine and citrus. Flavour is much the same full of pine and citrus, full Flavour and superb bitter taste but not as bitter as other west coast ipas. Very nice very tasty easily drinkable.

Poors jet black with a mocha head. Aroma is superb roast slight bacon and smoke. Flavour is bourban, molasses alcohol and a superb stout with plenty of chocolate and slight coffee. Taste is syrupy but not cloying which is a great balance. Great slow sipper.

Poors a very nice clear straw yellow with just enough white head and carbonation. Aroma is big and tasty full of citrus and a touch of pine. Taste is pleasant bitterness, nice clean malt palate that does not interfer at all with the hops. Its all about the hops this one and its done well. Very enjoyable iPa.
Poors a very nice clear dark copper. Aroma is of slight fruity hops and roasted grain. Taste is nice full body with a smooth but lingering bitterness. Tasty crisp filling beer.
Nice aroma of tropical fruits some lemon and lime. Intersting aroma and flavours. Light and easily drinkable beer.

Not the greatest iPa. Lacking in aroma and bitterness. Some pine and citrus, very slightly in the aroma. Does not follow through into flavours. Bit bland unfortunately. Tasted the apa alongside which had a lot more flavours and aroma!

Poors a deep clear dark coper. Minimal head retention but nice lacing down the glass. Aroma is whiskey and malt intertwind. Taste is sweet malt with a nice bitterness, long Finnish of both on the palate after. Not cloying or syrupy at all. Flavours is complex big and malty. Really enjoyable. Some nice warmth kicks in toward the end of the glass from the alcohol. Very smooth. Very dangerous and would appreciate another if not for the price tag. Great wee sipper to savor.

Nice session able stout. Poors a clear black with ruby highlights. Aroma of coffee slight chocolate and malt. Taste is bitter mocha, slight smoothness, porter like body. Over all was expecting a little more or something a little bit different but got a solid stout.
beer_name: Williams Brothers March of the Penguins

review_blob: Poors a ruby brown, nice creamy head but that disappears slowly. Aroma of slight malt, coffee and chocolate. All very subtle. Flavours are also very subtle. All about the taste and feel this beer. Nice creamy and mellow. Makes you want to slow down and enjoy it.
Poors a hazy golden orange. Aroma is a big mix up of tropical fruit, I think I pick out papaya? Taste is big and syrupy full bodied, a nice quiet sipper this one.

Poors a really nice clear yellow orange with lasting white head. Aroma is slight pine and passion fruit. Taste is a nice subtle bitterness, full bodied. Taste over all I wanted a bit more punch. Very nice, easy to drink.

Poors a bright clear yellow. Pure white head that disappears quickly. Aroma is tropical fruit and a touch of pine. Flavour is tropical fruit with pine in the back ground, grassy flavours come through occasionally. Big smooth bitterness and a full 8% make a tasty dangerously easily drinkable iPa.
beer_name: Golden Road Wolf Among Weeds IPA

review_blob: Poors black with tan head which disappear quickly. Aroma is of smoked roasted grains. Taste is mellow, roast, rich smoke. Big sweetness which is nice and plenty of body in the porter which I like. The smoke is subtle but builds and stays with you after the beer is finnished. Nice sessionable smokey porter.
beer_name: Wolf of the Willows Johnny Smoke Porter

review_blob: Very tasty saison. Poors sparkling clear golden with frothy white head. Nice saison yeast up front lemon and slight spice in the mix with barn and lawn mowing. Very thirst quenching. Would buy again.
Very nice, very drinkable ipa. Some subtle aroma of citrus and tropical fruits. Taste nice amount of bitterness. Some good body from the alcohol.

Wasnt sure what I was expecting from this beer Poored a nice clear pale yellow. Aroma was very slight lemon, nothing big. Taste was something different. Really nice mouth puckering sourness. Slight vinegar very dry but expremely nice. Will be buying again for the summer I feel.
beer_name: Two Metre Tall Derwent Clear Ale

review_blob:
Very nice easy drinking ipa. Poors a pleasant golden colour. Aroma of fruit and just slight pine. Pleasant bitterness. Tastenof malt and tropical fruity hops nicely balanced and just leaning toward hops.
Very nice easily drinkable ipa.

Big rich molasses dominates this imperial stout. Poors a nice pitch black with minimal tan head. Aroma is chocolate and coffee. Taste is thick, sweetness initially balanced but after taste is sickly. Flavour is coffee, chocolate and dominated by molasses. Some alcohol comes through strongly. Over all full flavoured but not the best imperial stout Ive had.
beer_name: Eel River Ravens Eye Imperial Stout

review_blob: Nice full flavoured stout. Poors a pitch black with minimal head. Aroma is of roasted grain with some nice coffee and chocolate. Taste is pleasant bitter. Flavour is a little harsh and rough. Over all a nice stout to have a couple of.

Very nice wee Porter. Was expecting big and bold got a tasty sessionable porter with a well balanced flavour and taste. Poors a nice almost pitch black with tan head. Aroma of roasted malt, slight coffee mixed in with chocolate. Taste is thin, easily drinkable and leaves room for more than one.
beer_name: Mountain Goat & Seven Seeds Seedy Goat Coffee Porter

review_blob: Big full flavoured dessert beer. Appearance is pitch black with a tan head. Aroma is big sweet almost pungent vanilla. Taste is strong, rich, roast and vanilla. Didnt need to drink the whole bottle would have been great with a dessert of some kind. May be something tart or bitter to balance.

Poors a black brown coke appearance. Slight lingering tan head. Aroma is molasses which follows through and dominates the beer for me. Some slight chocolate and nice malt but not the mellow smooth malty brownie bomb I was after. Love the molasses.

Pitch black poor with a long lasting mocha head. Aroma of chocolate and roast. Flavour is dusty chocolate with some dark fruits coming through in the background but mostly a delicious dry bitter chocolate flavour. Great beer.

Poor is clear yellow straw with minimal carbonation and a good amount of head. Aroma is grapefruit but not as intense as I was expecting, still very nice. Taste is bitter at the end a nice amount of sweetness to balance. Flavour is big grapefruit just a nice amount of piney resin.
Very good very nice big full flavoured ale.

Poors a clear hay with minimal head. Aroma is not as big as I was expecting but very pleasant and floral. Taste is bitter sweet very very smooth and the glass disappears just a little to quickly. Another tasty beer over all.
Great beer. Poors a pleasant amber, thin head. Aroma is slight pine and what could be the peach. Flavour is peach and a nice bitterness throughout. Easily drinkable, very enjoyable beer.

Very nice full flavoured sessionable pale ale. Poors a hazy hay yellow. Aroma is floral flavour is big full on and tasty. Tang,slight spice, very mourish. Taste is a nice pleasant bitterness and spice. A big flavoured beer. Could have many.
Big bitterness some light fruity aroma and taste but over all impression big and bitter.

Poors a clear deep straw yellow. Aroma is cascade and flavour follows on. Wish I could have this brew fresh from the tap because even though it has that awesome cascade aroma and flavour its faded with time and travel. Good beer none the less. Some really nice lingering bitterness.

An incredabily good beer. Poor is black with thin slightly off white head. Aroma is big resinous pine with dark rich chocolate. Flavour is resin, woody, chocolate, dark fruits and burnt brown sugar all combined. Bitter sweet and with a nice heat from the high alchol content this is a superb Complex siping in front of the fire beer.
beer_name: Founders Dark Penance Imperial Black IPA

review_blob: Poors a clear light amber out the bottle, nice thin lingering head. Aroma is very slight fruity hops, smells sweet. Taste is a good bitterness, soft and again lingering and dry. Tasty sessionable kind of Ipa nothing to over the top aroma and flavour wise but good lingering bitterness.

A very nice decadent beer. Poors a clear black. Thin coffee head lingers nicely. Aroma is chocolate and just a hint of cheery. Flavour is rich and warm. Nice chocolate. Great beer to sip quietly. Cheery feels a bit missing. Only negative of the beer not enough cheery but really tasty well balanced decadent beer.
Bit of a suprise this one. Some nice full on tropical fruit. Easily drinkable and sessionable. Tasty beer, thirst quenching with some nice aroma and flavour.
Hazy yellow golden poor. Subtle flavours. Refreshing but not a stand out beer for me.
Nice poor like a coke. Some nice coffee and chocolate just slight. Easily drunk with a thin body.
Really enjoyed this wee beer. Tasty, sessionable and refreshing. Has some nice subtle Flavours.

Poor is cloudy murky orange brown with thin head not lasting. Aroma some pine and barn like funk? Flavour is ripe fruits, slight pepper. Very interesting hop aroma and flavour. Not a bad beer, interesting but not one Togo in the top 5.

Tasty beer nice spice on the nose and follows through into the flavour. Beer is slightly chewy and sustainable interesting sweetness to it second to the berries? Really nice beer. Well balanced. Would drink this again and probably again.
Cloudy straw poor. Not much on the nose very slight pine. Some nice flavour though more pine and grapefruit big bitterness leaves mouth feeling dry. Not bad at all.
beer_name: Two Birds Wolf of the West
